  "topics": [
    "AUTHORIZATION"
  ],
  "statement": "Implement a simple user authorization system with two roles: 'admin' and 'user'. The system should allow admins to create and delete users, while users should only be able to read their own information.\n\nImplement the following endpoints:\n\n- POST /api/users: Create a new user.\n- GET /api/users/:id: Retrieve a user by ID.\n- DELETE /api/users/:id: Delete a user.\n\nAssume the user data is stored in an in-memory array for simplicity.\n\nThe user data should be sent in the following format:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n  \"role\": \"admin\"\n}\n```\n\nYou can add any additional endpoints or features as needed, but ensure they are properly authorized.",
  "constraints": [
    "Must use only the in-memory array provided in the starter code.",
    "Use the `express.json()` middleware to parse JSON bodies."
  ],
  "endpoints": [
    {
      "method": "POST",
      "path": "/api/users",
      "description": "Create a new user. Requires a JSON body with the user's name and role."
    },
    {
      "method": "GET",
      "path": "/api/users/:id",
      "description": "Retrieve a user by ID. Requires no body."
    },
    {
      "method": "DELETE",
      "path": "/api/users/:id",
      "description": "Delete a user by ID. Requires no body."
    }
  ],
  "mode": "solve",
